cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with a supervisory control problem for discrete-event systems, which is a topic in control theory and falls under the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category. The presence of an attacker and the need to consider observability in a new sense suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category. The use of automata and product automata in the paper suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) categories. Finally, the development of robust observers and the use of automata suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category.
